<p>China, Japan, Korea use the same notation as English-speaking nations in=
cluding India. Elsewhere, the same general principles are used, but the fig=
ures are often arranged differently.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Latin_America">Latin Americ=
a</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket"=
>[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DLong_divis=
ion&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D10" title=3D"Edit section: Latin Americ=
a"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></div>
<p>In <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Latin_America" title=3D"Lati=
n America">Latin America</a> (except <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Argentina" title=3D"Argentina">Argentina</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Bolivia" title=3D"Bolivia">Bolivia</a>, <a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mexico" title=3D"Mexico">Mexico</a>, <a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colombia" title=3D"Colombia">Colombia</a>, <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paraguay" title=3D"Paraguay">Paraguay</a>=
, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Venezuela" title=3D"Venezuela">V=
enezuela</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uruguay" title=3D"Ur=
uguay">Uruguay</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brazil" tit=
le=3D"Brazil">Brazil</a>), the calculation is almost exactly the same, but =
is written down differently as shown below with the same two examples used =
above. Usually the quotient is written under a bar drawn under the divisor.=
 A long vertical line is sometimes drawn to the right of the calculations.
</p>
<pre>     500 =C3=B7 4 =3D  <span style=3D"color: red;">1</span><span style=
=3D"color: green;">2</span><span style=3D"color: blue;">5</span>   (Explana=
tions)=20
     <u>4</u>                ( 4 =C3=97  <span style=3D"color: red;">1</spa=
n> =3D  4)
     <span style=3D"color: darkorange;">1</span>0               ( 5 -  4 =
=3D  <span style=3D"color: darkorange;">1</span>)
      <u>8</u>               ( 4 =C3=97  <span style=3D"color: green;">2</s=
pan> =3D  8)
      <span style=3D"color: darkcyan;">2</span>0              (10 -  8 =3D =
 <span style=3D"color: darkcyan;">2</span>)
      <u>20</u>              ( 4 =C3=97  <span style=3D"color: blue;">5</sp=
an> =3D 20)
       0              (20 - 20 =3D  0)
</pre>
<p>and
</p>
<pre>     127 =C3=B7 4 =3D 31.75
     <u>124</u>                            =20
       30      (bring down 0; decimal to quotient)
       <u>28</u>      (7 =C3=97 4 =3D 28)
        20     (an additional zero is added)
        <u>20</u>     (5 =C3=97 4 =3D 20)
          0
</pre>
<p>In <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mexico" title=3D"Mexico">Mex=
ico</a>, the English-speaking world notation is used, except that only the =
result of the subtraction is annotated and the calculation is done mentally=
, as shown below:
</p>
<pre>    <u> <span style=3D"color: red;">1</span><span style=3D"color: gree=
n;">2</span><span style=3D"color: blue;">5</span></u>     (Explanations)
   4)500
     <span style=3D"color: darkorange;">1</span>0      ( 5 -  4 =3D <span s=
tyle=3D"color: darkorange;">1</span>)
      <span style=3D"color: darkcyan;">2</span>0     (10 -  8 =3D <span sty=
le=3D"color: darkcyan;">2</span>)
       0     (20 - 20 =3D 0)
</pre>
<p>In <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bolivia" title=3D"Bolivia">B=
olivia</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brazil" title=3D"Brazi=
l">Brazil</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paraguay" title=3D"=
Paraguay">Paraguay</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Venezuela"=
 title=3D"Venezuela">Venezuela</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/French_Canadians" title=3D"French Canadians">French-speaking Canada</a>, =
<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colombia" title=3D"Colombia">Colom=
bia</a>, and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peru" title=3D"Peru">=
Peru</a>, the European notation (see below) is used, except that the quotie=
nt is not separated by a vertical line, as shown below:
</p>
<pre>    127|<u>4    </u>
   =E2=88=92<u>124</u> 31,75
      30
     =E2=88=92<u>28</u>
       20
      =E2=88=92<u>20</u>
        0
</pre>
<p>Same procedure applies in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mexic=
o" title=3D"Mexico">Mexico</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ur=
uguay" title=3D"Uruguay">Uruguay</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Argentina" title=3D"Argentina">Argentina</a>, only the result of the=
 subtraction is annotated and the calculation is done mentally.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Eurasia">Eurasia</h3><span =
class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DLong_division&amp;acti=
on=3Dedit&amp;section=3D11" title=3D"Edit section: Eurasia"><span>edit</spa=
n></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>In Spain, Italy, France, Portugal, Lithuania, Romania, Turkey, Greece, B=
elgium, Belarus, Ukraine, and Russia, the divisor is to the right of the di=
vidend, and separated by a vertical bar. The division also occurs in the co=
lumn, but the quotient (result) is written below the divider, and separated=
 by the horizontal line. The same method is used in Iran, Vietnam, and Mong=
olia.
</p>
<pre>    127|<u>4    </u>
   =E2=88=92<u>124</u>|31,75
      30
     =E2=88=92<u>28</u>
       20
      =E2=88=92<u>20</u>
        0
</pre>
<p>In Cyprus, as well as in France, a long vertical bar separates the divid=
end and subsequent subtractions from the quotient and divisor, as in the <a=
 href=3D"https://fr.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poser_une_division#M%C3%A9thode_clas=
sique" class=3D"extiw" title=3D"fr:Poser une division">example</a> below of=
 6359 divided by 17, which is 374 with a remainder of 1.
</p>
<pre>    6359|<u>17    </u>
   =E2=88=92<u>51</u>  |374
    125 |
   =E2=88=92<u>119</u> |
      69|
     =E2=88=92<u>68</u>|
       1|
</pre>
<p>Decimal numbers are not divided directly, the dividend and divisor are m=
ultiplied by a power of ten so that the division involves two whole numbers=
. Therefore, if one were dividing 12,7 by 0,4 (commas being used instead of=
 decimal points), the dividend and divisor would first be changed to 127 an=
d 4, and then the division would proceed as above.
</p><p>In <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Austria" title=3D"Austri=
a">Austria</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Germany" title=3D"=
Germany">Germany</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Switzerla=
nd" title=3D"Switzerland">Switzerland</a>, the notational form of a normal =
equation is used. &lt;dividend&gt;&nbsp;: &lt;divisor&gt; =3D &lt;quotient&=
gt;, with the colon ":" denoting a binary infix symbol for the division ope=
rator (analogous to "/" or "=C3=B7"). In these regions the decimal separato=
r is written as a comma. (cf. first section of Latin American countries abo=
ve, where it's done virtually the same way):
</p>
<pre>    127&nbsp;: 4 =3D 31,75
   =E2=88=92<u>12</u>
     07
     =E2=88=92<u>4</u>
      30
     =E2=88=92<u>28</u>
       20
      =E2=88=92<u>20</u>
        0
</pre>
<p>The same notation is adopted in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Denmark" title=3D"Denmark">Denmark</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Norway" title=3D"Norway">Norway</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia=
.org/wiki/Bulgaria" title=3D"Bulgaria">Bulgaria</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/North_Macedonia" title=3D"North Macedonia">North Macedon=
ia</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poland" title=3D"Poland">P=
oland</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Croatia" title=3D"Croat=
ia">Croatia</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Slovenia" title=
=3D"Slovenia">Slovenia</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hungar=
y" title=3D"Hungary">Hungary</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/=
Czech_Republic" title=3D"Czech Republic">Czech Republic</a>, <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Slovakia" title=3D"Slovakia">Slovakia</a>, <a hr=
ef=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vietnam" title=3D"Vietnam">Vietnam</a> =
and in <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Serbia" title=3D"Serbia">Se=
rbia</a>.
</p><p>In the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Netherlands" title=
=3D"Netherlands">Netherlands</a>, the following notation is used:
</p>
<pre>   12 / 135 \ 11,25
        <u>12</u>
         15
         <u>12</u>
          30
          <u>24</u>
           60
           <u>60</u>
            0
</pre>
<p>In <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Finland" title=3D"Finland">F=
inland</a>, the Italian method detailed above was replaced by the Anglo-Ame=
rican one in the 1970s. In the early 2000s, however, some textbooks have ad=
opted the German method as it retains the order between the divisor and the=
 dividend.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-11" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en=
.wikipedia.org/wiki/Long_division#cite_note-11"><span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">[</span>11<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Algorithm_for_arbitrary_bas=
e">Algorithm for arbitrary base</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span cl=
ass=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
w/index.php?title=3DLong_division&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D12" title=
=3D"Edit section: Algorithm for arbitrary base"><span>edit</span></a><span =
class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
See also: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Division_algorithm#Long_=
division" title=3D"Division algorithm">Division algorithm =C2=A7&nbsp;Long =
division</a></div>
<p>Every <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Natural_number" title=3D"=
Natural number">natural number</a> <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math=
-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y=
" style=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathM=
